        <header class="text-center my-4">
            <h1 class="display-4">GST Rate Deductions Across Sectors: A Game-Changer for E-commerce Businesses</h1>
            <p class="lead text-muted">Estimated Reading Time: 12-15 minutes</p>
        </header>

        <section id="introduction">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>The Goods and Services Tax (GST) landscape in India has undergone significant transformations since its
                implementation in 2017. With periodic rate revisions and deductions across various sectors, these
                changes have created ripple effects throughout the e-commerce ecosystem. Understanding these deductions
                and their implications is crucial for businesses looking to optimize their operations and enhance
                profitability in the digital marketplace.</p>
            <p>This comprehensive analysis explores the recent GST rate deductions across different sectors, their
                profound impact on e-commerce businesses, and strategic approaches to leverage these changes for
                competitive advantage.</p>
        </section>

        ---

        <section id="gst-rate-structure">
            <h2>Overview of GST Rate Structure</h2>
            <p>Before diving into sector-specific deductions, it's essential to understand the current GST slab
                structure in India:</p>
            <div class="table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-striped table-bordered">
                    <thead class="thead-dark">
                        <tr>
                            <th>GST Slab</th>
                            <th>Product Categories</th>
                            <th>E-commerce Relevance</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td>0%</td>
                            <td>Essential items (unbranded cereals, fresh vegetables)</td>
                            <td>Limited online presence</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>5%</td>
                            <td>Basic necessities, economy products</td>
                            <td>Growing e-commerce segment</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>12%</td>
                            <td>Standard goods and services</td>
                            <td>Moderate e-commerce activity</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>18%</td>
                            <td>Most products and services</td>
                            <td>High e-commerce volume</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>28%</td>
                            <td>Luxury and sin goods</td>
                            <td>Premium e-commerce segment</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </section>

